Today is marked as the International Day of UN Peacekeepers. The South African National Defence Force honours SANDF members who died while serving under the UN peacekeeping missions flag, for their courage,service and sacrifices. eNCA's Govan Whittles has more on the story. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African National Defence Force honoured its members who died while serving under the UN peacekeeping missions flag. READ:Â Modise: SANDF short of resources The fallen soldiers were recognised for their courage, service and sacrifices. To mark the International Day of UN peacekeepers, Deputy Minister of Defence Thabang Makwetla and families also laid wreaths at the Peacekeepers Memorial.